When working with mdadm, which command- line argument is used to specify things likestriping and parity?
A)  - - layout
B)  - R
C)  - - level
D)  - x
A
A. Parity and striping are configured using - - layout or - p. The - x option specifies sparedevices while - R starts the array. The - - level option can be used to set the type of RAID,such as mirroring (RAID1) or striping (RAID5).
